      "span_text": "Noise is a general problem in diffusion MR imaging acquisitions, and its effects have been investigated extensively.  Using higher b-values in DKI acquisitions increases the sensitivity of the measurement to noise and, therefore, the possibility that the diffusion and kurtosis parameter estimates will vary from their true values, causing erroneous inferences.",
